{{Orphan|date=February 2009}} {{Infobox music festival | name =Wooden Octopus Skull Experimental Musick PFestival | image = | caption = | location =[[Seattle|Seattle, WA]] | years_active =2005-present | founders =[[Enterruption]] and [[Psychform Records]] | dates = | genre = [[Experimental music]], [[noise music]] | attendance = | capacity = | website = }} The '''''Wooden Octopus Skull Experimental Musick PFestival''''' is a [[noise music|noise]] and experimental music festival held annually, on the second weekend of September, in [[Seattle|Seattle, WA]]. It is primarily sponsored by [[Enterruption]] and [[Psychform Records]].
== 2005 == The first festival was held in 2005. It was widely assumed to be the continuation of the Seattle Noise Festival; however, the PFestival was a completely separate entity with no relation whatsoever to SNF.
Each day of Wooden Octopus Skull was held in a different venue.
{| class="wikitable" |- ! Date ! Venue ! Performers |- | Thursday, September 8 | [[Sunset Tavern]] | [[Portland Bike Ensemble]], [[Metalux]], [[Anti-Ear]], [[Noggin (band)|Noggin]], [[blackhumour]] |- | Friday, September 9 | [[Re-Bar]] | [[John Wiese]], [[the Haters]], [[Emil Beaulieau]], [[SIXES]], [[Gerritt]], [[Bacillus]] |- | Saturday, September 10 (Afternoon) | [[The Funhouse (Seattle)|The Funhouse]] | [[Vertonen]], [[Rubber-O-Cement]], [[Tarantism]], [[Panicsville]], [[Loachfillet]] |- | Saturday, September 10 (Evening) | [[Re-Bar]] | [[Caroliner Rainbow Scratched Soaproot and Candle Dinner]], [[Fe-Mail]], [[Smegma (band)|Smegma]], [[Aaron Dilloway]], [[Withdrawal Method]] |- | Sunday, September 11 (Afternoon) | [[The Funhouse (Seattle)|The Funhouse]] | [[Hans Grusel's Krankenkabinet]], [[Irr.App.(ext.)]], [[Climax Golden Twins]], [[Bill Horist]], [[Broken Penis Orchestra]] |- | Sunday, September 11 (Evening) | [[The Baltic Room]] | [[Steven Stapleton]], [[Spider Compass Good Crime Band]], [[Tom Recchion]], [[Herb Diamante]], [[Broken Human Machine]] |}
== 2006 == For 2006, the festival was held in a single location, [[The Conjuring Room]], and the afternoon shows were eliminated. The first two nights were organized as themed mini-festivals.
